# Types: thesis | hw | notes | fix | docs | chore | admin
# Scope: subfolder or chapter/course, e.g. galois, topology, cubic-reciprocity
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# No more than 50 chars. #### 50 chars is here:  #

# Leave the next line blank

# Body - for thesis commits, note the *why* (what changed mathematically, what feedback prompted it)
# Wrap at 72 chars. ################################## which is here:  #

# The following fields are optional. Fill them out if they apply.
# Footer:
# Advisor:
# Refs: [[note link]]
#
# Types:
# thesis  Thesis content — new sections, argument changes, proof writeups
# hw      Homework — new problem sets, corrections, resubmissions
# notes   Vault content — new/updated notes, restructuring links
# fix     Correcting an error (a wrong proof step, a typo that changes meaning, a broken build)
# docs    README, this workflow doc, template changes
# chore   Repo maintenance — gitignore, folder reorg, CI config
# admin   Paperwork, proposals, committee docs
#
# Scope examples:
# thesis(galois): draft section on splitting fields
# thesis(cubic-reciprocity): rework proof of prop 3.2
# hw(topology): submit hw04
# hw(real-analysis): correct hw02 problem 3, resubmit
# notes(thesis): link cubic reciprocity concept note to MOC
# notes(topology): add lecture note 2026-08-25
# fix(thesis): correct sign error in eisenstein criterion proof
# docs(vault): update workflow doc with dataview section
# chore(vault): gitignore obsidian workspace state
# admin(proposal): add signed thesis proposal PDF
